{
  "stem": "490.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a matter of fact, our-- if I were to describe the type of schools we had, when I was, remember, 15, we practiced-- we practiced-- today, I would call it 'transcendental meditation.' And we practiced-- when I was 15, already, the type of education we had-- it was-- it was transcendental meditation, but with a religious motive, not just with, like, nonsense to keep on repeating and to keep on killing your-- your-- your brain or killing your-- not to think of anything, just to have your mind blank.",
      "word_count": 90
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we had to-- we practiced transcendental meditation with a reason, that-- that things are not-- to-- to assure you that things are not done just because it is-- it is there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything has a reason, and everything has-- has a-- a-- a plan for you.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was a very strong way of building youngsters.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those youngsters, they-- we were all friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all talked our-- to each other like brothers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because most of the time, we all needed each other, because they went away from their home and they missed probably their sisters and brothers, and neither were in the yeshiva, in the school.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were together, having-- facing the same problems.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So those were my best friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, of course, the teachers, they were enormous people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were people-- we used to call them-- they were-- [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We say-- we used to say in-- there's in Hebrew, it happened to Jacob when he left-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] when he ran away from-- from Esau.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the way, he dreamt that there was a ladder standing on the ground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And reached up to the sky.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he saw the angels going up and down.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, the commentators say that these angels were a change of guards.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
